Patients with hormone-sensitive prostate cancer and rising PSA, after primary tumor treatment, will be treated with the P501-AS15 vaccine as out-patients.

 The maximum dose will be 16 vaccinations, given over a period of approximately one year.

 Thereafter, the patients' long-term safety and PSA status will be followed over a period of approximately 11 months.

